      • compare

        public int compare(java.lang.Object one,
                   java.lang.Object two)
        Determines if one elements is less, equal or greater than other. A value < 0 indicates that one is less than two, a value = 0 indicates that one is equal to two and a value > 0 indicates that one is greater than two
        Specified by:
        compare in class Order<java.lang.Object>
        Parameters:
        one - First object to be compared
        two - Second object to be compared
        Returns:
        a value < 0 if one < two, 0 if one == two and > 0 if one > two.
